name: undecaprenyl-diphosphate phosphatase
reaction: ditrans,octacis-undecaprenyl diphosphate + H2O = ditrans,octacis-undecaprenyl phosphate + phosphate [RN:R05627]
comment: Isolated from the bacteria Micrococcus lysodeikticus [1], Escherichia coli [2,3,5,6] and Bacillus subtilis [4]. The product of the reaction, ditrans,octacis-undecaprenyl phosphate, is essential for cell wall polysaccharide biosynthesis in these strains.
